<TITLE> Victory Day Hockey starts Sunday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 29 (bdnews24.com)  The Dhaka Bank Victory Day Hockey Tournament gets underway Sunday with Bangladesh Army taking on Bangladesh Navy in the opening match at Moulana Bhasani National Hockey Stadium. A total of six teams will take part in the league basis meet, said Bangladesh Hockey Federation (BHF) general secretary Sajed AA Adel at a press conference at the federation's conference room Saturday. Two top teams will play the final on January 12. Dhaka Bank, which has been attached with the BHF, will bear expenses estimated at Tk 1.2 lakh. "We have come forward to help country's hockey after responding to the appeal of the National Sports Council Chairman and Army Chief General Moeen U Ahmed," said Dhaka Bank deputy managerial director Tanvir Rahim. "We have a plan to spread hockey across the country by holding the Victory Day Hockey Tournament and we want to grant an annual budget to the federation in this regard," said Rahim. BHF joint secretaries Khaza Manjur Nadim, Alamgir Kabir and tournament committee secretary Mirza Farid Ahmed were among others present. Participating teams are Bangladesh Krira Shikkha Protisthan, Sonali Bank SRC, Bangladesh Army, Bangladesh Navy, Bangladesh Air Force and Barnak Samaj. 
